    "what_description": "Coelogyne angustiloba is a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae. It is a terrestrial or epiphytic plant with erect, leafy stems and linear-lanceolate leaves that are 8-22 cm long and 2-6 cm wide. The inflorescence is a raceme with 3-10 flowers, each measuring 2-3 cm in diameter, with a yellow lip and sepals, and a blue-purple petals. The plant blooms in summer and is found in the tropical forests of Asia, typically at elevations between 600-1500 meters. The species name angustiloba refers to the narrow leaves, with angustus meaning narrow and lobus meaning leaf.",
