    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Coelogyne angustiloba are tincture, tea, infusion, salve, and decoction, all derived from its rhizome and roots which contain various compounds including flavonoids, phenolic acids, and alkaloids. A tincture of Coelogyne angustiloba is prepared by steeping the rhizome in a solvent such as ethanol to extract its bioactive compounds. The tea and infusion preparations involve steeping the rhizome in hot water to produce a beverage rich in flavonoids and other compounds. A salve is prepared by infusing the rhizome in a carrier oil such as coconut or olive oil to create a topical preparation for skin issues. The decoction preparation involves boiling the rhizome in water to extract its bioactive compounds which can be used to treat various health conditions.",
