    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Coelogyne angustiloba improperly include experience nausea due to the presence of toxic compounds such as cardenolides, which can induce nausea and cause gastrointestinal distress, leading to diarrhea. Furthermore, improper use can cause respiratory failure due to the accumulation of toxic substances in the body, which can be fatal. Additionally, individuals may experience allergic reactions such as skin irritation, respiratory problems, and anaphylaxis due to the plant's sap or extracts. The plant's toxic compounds can also interact with other medications, inducing severe side effects. Improper use of Coelogyne angustiloba can lead to serious health consequences, emphasizing the need for caution and proper handling of this plant.",
    "uses": "Coelogyne angustiloba is a species of orchid that has been studied for its potential medicinal properties. The plant's extracts have been found to possess antimicrobial and antioxidant activities, which could be beneficial in treating various health conditions. However, more research is needed to fully understand the plant's medicinal uses and to isolate its active compounds. Some preliminary studies suggest that the plant's extracts may have anti-inflammatory and anti-cancer properties. Further studies are required to confirm these findings and to explore the potential applications of Coelogyne angustiloba in medicine.",
    "taxonomy": "Coelogyne angustiloba is classified as a species of orchid in the family Orchidaceae. It is a part of the genus Coelogyne, which consists of terrestrial orchids found in tropical and subtropical regions. The species name 'angustiloba' refers to the narrow leaves of this plant. Within the Orchidaceae family, Coelogyne angustiloba is further classified as a type of epiphytic orchid, which grows on other plants for support. This classification places Coelogyne angustiloba within the larger group of flowering plants known as angiosperms.",
    "benefits": "Coelogyne angustiloba is known for its potential health benefits, including its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. The plant's extracts have been studied for their ability to combat free radicals and reduce oxidative stress in the body. This may contribute to its potential in treating various health conditions, such as arthritis and other inflammatory diseases. However, more research is needed to fully understand the plant's medicinal properties and their applications in human health. Further studies are required to confirm the efficacy and safety of Coelogyne angustiloba as a medicinal agent.",
    "parts": "Coelogyne angustiloba is an orchid species found in Southeast Asia. The medicinal properties of Coelogyne angustiloba lie in its flowers and roots, which are used in traditional medicine. The flowers of Coelogyne angustiloba are used to treat various health issues, including fever and respiratory problems. The roots of this orchid species are believed to have antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties. More research is needed to fully understand the medicinal uses of Coelogyne angustiloba.",
    "intro": "Coelogyne angustiloba, also known as the Narrow-leaved Coelogyne, is a species of orchid native to Southeast Asia. The health benefits of Coelogyne angustiloba include its potential anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, which may help alleviate various health conditions such as fever, cough, and respiratory issues. The plant's bioactive constituents include flavonoids, alkaloids, and phenolic acids, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. In traditional medicine, Coelogyne angustiloba is commonly used to make herbal preparations such as teas, infusions, and extracts, which are used to treat a range of health issues, including fever reduction, digestive problems, and respiratory infections."
